As a single elimination tournament after the group stages, World Cups can be difficult to predict as all it takes is a single mistake against a good team to sink your hopes for the tournament. That said, history would dictate that the winner is usually a top footballing nation filled with quality players all over the pitch. It is very rare that we see deep Cinderella runs deep into the Semis and Final of the tournament. Being the best far from guarantees success, but the winner is usually one of the best teamsLooking at the current field for this World Cup I would classify team with a reasonable shot at winning into the following teirs:
